com.github.macgregor.alexandria

Class Config.DocumentMetadata

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.macgregor.alexandria.Config.DocumentMetadata
  • Enclosing class:
    Config

    public static class Config.DocumentMetadata
extends Object
    Metadata used to index a document for tracking and syncing purposes. Alexandria uses this metadata to determine what state the document is in, e.g. does it need to be created on the remote, has it already been deleted from the remote, etc. Remote implementations will also use it to track remote specific metadata in extraProps, for example a document id needed to interact with the document via rest. Only the remote implementation will be aware of and use these special properties, core document processing will only use declared fields.

    • Field Detail

      • sourcePath

        @NonNull
protected Path sourcePath
        File path to the indexed document which may or may not exist. At runtime, this will be an absolute path, but when persisted it will be converted to a path relative to Context.configPath.
        See Also:
        Context.makePathsAbsolute(), Context.makePathsRelative()

      • title

        @NonNull
protected String title
        Title of the document. The indexing phase will default this to the file name.

      • remoteUri

        protected Optional<URI> remoteUri
        Remote address of the document if it already exists on the remote. Default: none. (this will trigger a create) If not set, triggers a create when the sync phase is executed. The default state is to create the document. If it already exists before using Alexandria, be sure to manually add the remote uri so that the remote document is updated instead of duplicated. Remotes may or may not use this URI exactly to interact with the remote. For example, Jive has different addresses for documents you interact with in a browser than documents you interact with through rest, so it has to convert this human URI to a computer one.

      • tags

        protected Optional<List<String>> tags
        Tags to add to the document. Default: empty list.

      • sourceChecksum

        protected Optional<Long> sourceChecksum
        Simple file checksum on the source file path used to trigger updates. Default: none.

      • convertedChecksum

        protected Optional<Long> convertedChecksum
        Simple file checksum on the converted file path used to trigger conversion. Default: none.

      • createdOn

      • lastUpdated
